window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A boy discovers the answer to one of the great urban mysteries: Why are pigeons always pooping in parks? A second-grade class learns why they should always be nice to their math teacher.... An ancient predator uses the internet to search out its prey. A young girl and her little brother escape a campfire weenie only to encounter something even more terrifying: a troop of Girl Scouts singing campfire songs.</p> <p>For this, his third collection of warped and creepy \"weenie\" tales, critically-acclaimed author and master of the macabre David Lubar traveled deep into the shadowy corners of his mind, looking for new ways to amuse and terrify his listeners. And in the tradition of <i>In the Land of the Lawn Weenies</i> and <i>Invasion of the Road Weenies</i>, he reveals the inspiration behind each of the 35 stories at the end of the book.</p>"; 
